quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  10,54,"Every soul that has done wrong, if it had whatever is in the earth, would seek to ransom itself therewith. They will utter their repentance when they see the torment; but it shall be decided between them with justice, nor shall they be wronged"
  10,55,Is it not the case that to Allah belongs all that is in the heavens and in the earth? Is it not the case that the promise of Allah is certainly true? But most of them understand not
  10,56,"Is it He Who gives life and He Who takes it, and unto Him shall you all be returned"
  10,57,"O mankind! There has come to you a direction (guidance, exhortation) from your Lord, and a healing for the disease in your breasts, and a guidance and a mercy for believers"
  10,58,"Say, \"In the grace of Allah and in His mercy let them rejoice!\" It is better than that (wealth) which they hoard"
  10,59,"Say, \"See you what Allah has sent down to you for sustenance? Yet you have made some unlawful and some lawful. Say, \"Has Allah permitted you, or do you invent lies concerning Allah"
  10,60,"What will those who invent lies concerning Allah think on the Day of Resurrection? Verily, Allah is truly Bountiful towards mankind, but most of them give no thanks"
  10,61,"Thee (Muhammad) are not occupied with any business, nor recite you a lecture from this Scripture, and you (mankind) perform no act, but We are Witness when you are engaged therein: nor does the weight of an atom escape your Lord in the earth or in heaven"